N:vibe-kanban
V:2.0.0
D:Board-first control plane for AI coding agents. Use when the real job is managing task cards, isolated workspaces/worktrees, review queues, retries, and PR handoff for bounded coding tasks — not just prompting one agent once.
G:vibe-kanban kanban kanbanview task-board workspace-board review-queue multi-agent worktree github-pr claude-code codex gemini opencode
U[6]:
  Run a visual board for bounded coding tasks with isolated workspaces
  Track Running -> Review -> Done state for parallel coding-agent work
  Compare agent attempts and retry based on diff/review evidence
  Keep review plus PR handoff explicit instead of relying on chat memory
  Manage worktree/branch cleanup as part of the board workflow
  Route planning-only or non-code workflows away before opening a board
S[5]{n,action,details}:
  1,Classify,Decide whether the request truly needs a coding board/workspace loop
  2,Split,Keep one bounded coding task per card/workspace
  3,Run,Start the board and launch isolated workspaces for selected agents
  4,Review,Inspect diffs/logs and choose retry split approve or PR handoff
  5,Cleanup,Close stale cards prune worktrees and clean leftover branches/servers
R[5]:
  Use vibe-kanban only when board control review and worktree isolation matter
  Prefer board-first then PR handoff for fast local iteration on shared repos
  Limit parallel cards to what a human reviewer can actually keep up with
  Route PM marketing and non-code game-production coordination to other skills
  Use MCP only when programmatic board control materially helps
E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Parallel bugfix board","Set up a board so Claude and Codex each handle one frontend bug and I can review diffs before PRs","Create bounded cards and isolated workspaces with review -> PR flow"
  "Agent comparison","Run two agents on the same API bug so I can compare their diffs","Create comparison-friendly workspaces and preserve review criteria"
  "Planning only","Help me break this migration into phases before coding starts","Route to task-planning or plannotator instead of opening a board"
  "Marketing board","I need a board for content calendar approvals and launch copy revisions","Route to marketing-automation or PM/content workflow skills"
T[3]{problem,solution}:
  "Cards keep stalling","Split them smaller and reduce parallel workspaces"
  "Review backlog grows","Switch to PR-first review or lower active card count"
  "Worktree mess","Run cleanup scripts plus git worktree list/prune and close stale cards"
